caption: César Auguste-Jean-Guillaume-Hubert Franck /se'zaʁ fʁɑ̃k/ (Liège, 10 December 1822 – Paris, 8 November 1890) was a Belgian composer, organist and teacher of music. He is one of the most important figures of French musical life in the second half of the 19th century.
Beautiful tribute to César Franck (1822-1890) who was a Belgian-French teacher, organist and composer. He was organist of the Ste Clotilde basilica from 1858 to 1890. Work created by Alfred Lenoir.
I like the location of this statue with a flower bed at its feet. The distance is good to observe it well.
Organist Cesar Franck was the organist in Sainte-Clotilde for 32 years and his tribute is in the square in front of the Church.
